Private OpenBSD ports skeleton.

Don't forget to "git config user.email alice@example.org" or
 "git config --global user.email alice@example.org".


* bsd.port.mk port maintainer visible changes:

** OPENBSD_5_1

  - PROPERTIES variable
  - BASESYSCONFDIR

** OPENBSD_5_0

  - remove USE_MOTIF
  - support of xz
  - Add infrastructure for ccache in port builds.
  - regress-depends-list

** OPENBSD_4_9

  - allow BUILD_DEPENDS = somepath>=version:patch
  - Bye bye USE_X11. From now on, building ports requires X11BASE. (1.1043)
  - USE_GROFF

** OPENBSD_4_8 (bsd.port.mk,v 1.1026 2010/08/07)

  - PLIST_DB ?= ${PORTSDIR}/plist/${MACHINE_ARCH}
  - Remove redundant variables OPSYS and OPSYS_VER
  - Support REVISION & EPOCH
  - BROKEN-${ARCH}
  - Override MAKE in CONFIGURE_ENV when USE_GMAKE


** OPENBSD_4_7 (bsd.port.mk,v 1.979 2010/03/05)

  - Add mips64el to LP64_ARCHS.
  - Allow USE_LIBTOOL to be set to 'gnu';  'gnu' and 'yes' do the same for now.

** OPENBSD_4_6 (bsd.port.mk,v 1.967 2009/06/17)



